description: Students analyze mechanical principles in depth as they affect human motion. Topics include study of muscular and skeletal systems, skill analysis, and motion measurement techniques. The course included a laboratory component. Prerequisite: Biology 123 or consent of instructor.
name: Biomechanics
notes: Students in PE Theory 374 must also register for lab PE Theory 374L.

revisions.prerequisites: Prerequisite: Biology 123 or consent of instructor.
